        <div class="section-eyebrow">My Philosophy</div>
        <h2>The best offense is a <em>good defense.</em></h2>
        <p class="body-text">I come to every project prepared. That means doing the research before the design, understanding the learner before writing the objectives, and anticipating the edge cases before launch. Preparation isn't caution — it's what makes bold design possible.</p>
        <p class="body-text">At the same time, I've learned that the best-prepared designers are also the best at pivoting. Learner data, SME feedback, classroom reality — these things reshape every project. I stay ready to adapt without losing the thread of what the learning needs to do.</p>
        <p class="body-text">I believe in accessible education for everyone. I've built my career on Open Educational Resources because high-quality learning shouldn't be a privilege. That conviction shapes every design decision I make.</p>
        <blockquote class="philosophy-quote">"Learning is the only thing the mind never exhausts, never fears, and never regrets." — Leonardo Da Vinci</blockquote>
